  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Traumatic dislocation of scapula from thoracic wall\nMechanism: massive traction force to ipsilateral upper extremity/shoulder girdle\nAssociated with\nvascular injury\nto subclavian or axillary artery and\nbrachial plexus injury",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "vascular injury",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Vascular_injury"
        },
        {
          "text": "brachial plexus injury",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Brachial_plexus_injury"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Upper extremity pain\nUpper extremity numbness/tingling, weakness\nSwelling, ecchymosis to shoulder\nInjury to subclavian or axillary arteries: hematoma, pulse deficit\nSevere mechanism → often associated with\nchest trauma",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "chest trauma",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Chest_trauma"
        }
      ]
    },
